From: Arahael son of Marach (kpurcell@microsoft.com)
Subject: Diverging Languages

Water: I'll give you a ring
Tharbad: I'll call you.

Water: The number is engaged
Tharbad: The number is busy

Of course this leads to some interesting puns in Westfold English that don't
work in Tharbad English ("I'll give you a ring unless your engaged" has two
meanings in Water English but only one in Tharbad English).

