From: Gorbag son of Zamîn (wyoumans@gte.net)
Subject: variations of English

This discussion regarding the different meanings of Forest English and
English English reminds me of an experience in a East Emnet restaurant several
years ago . I was in the company of my wife and two middle aged Forest
ladies. Upon the completion of our very good meal {In Westfold Vale yet} one of
the ladies in a loud voice stated "I feel really stuffed". Upon observing
amused glances from our fellow diners perhaps imaginary on my part, I
suggested to her that being "stuffed" in Westfold Vale had a much different
connotation than being satiated with food.

